OL,6,G1987 In the early hours of the
OL,7,Gmorning, a major storm hit the south
OL,8,Gof England. BBC Television Centre lost
OL,9,Gits main power supply. Via a back-up
OL,10,Ggenerator NC1 (Network Control for BBC
OL,11,GOne) kept BBC One on air, with an
OL,12,Gimpromptu edition of BBC Breakfast
OL,13,GTime, presented by Nicholas Witchell
OL,14,Gfrom the BBC One continuity studio
OL,15,G(NC1 Con), also known as The Broom
OL,16,GCupboard by viewers of CBBC. The
OL,17,Gprogramme later switched to a
OL,18,Gtemporary studio.JTV-am was initially
OL,19,Gbroadcast from a small studio at
OL,20,GThames TV before power was restored at
OL,21,Gits main studios in Camden.JAlthough
OL,22,GBBC Two was not due on air until 9am,
OL,23,Gwith Pages from Ceefax, followed by
OL,24,GDaytime on Two at 9.30pm, an apology
OL,25,Gcaption is believed to have been in
OL,26,Gplace (accompanied by music) from c.
