OL,6,F1991 Following changes to the system
OL,7,Fof ITV licence allocation laid out in
OL,8,FThe Broadcasting Act 1990, the
OL,9,FIndependent Television Commission
OL,10,Ftoday announced the results of the
OL,11,Ffranchise round, for licences
OL,12,Fbeginning 1st January 1993.J- Thames `
OL,13,Fthe biggest programme supplier to the
OL,14,FITV network ` was outbid by
OL,15,Fbroadcasting and media services
OL,16,Fcompany, Carlton Television.J- TV-am
OL,17,Fwas outbid by #20m by Sunrise TV.J-
OL,18,FTVS failed to renew its licence
OL,19,Fbecause it bid too much ` Meridian
OL,20,FBroadcasting won that franchise.J- TSW
OL,21,Flost out to Westcountry TV, despite
OL,22,Fbidding more.JRELATED ARTICLE:
OL,23,FReflections on the 1991 franchise
OL,24,Fauction.
